event: tool_result
data: {"name":"incident_resolve","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Incident INC-20260221-0001 resolved\n\n🟠 SEV2 | ✅ RESOLVED\nID: INC-20260221-0001\nTitle: VAL-04 Test: API Latency Spike\nService: openagentic-api\nCreated: 2026-02-21T00:31:34.975257Z\n\nDescription: Automated test - elevated p99 latency detected\nRoot Cause: Primary latency contributor: PostgreSQL foreign key race condition in user_query_audit table. The API audit middleware attempts to INSERT audit records referencing message_id before the parent message row is committed, causing FK constraint violations at ~11.6 errors/min. Secondary contributors: (a) code-manager and openagentic-synth pods reporting DOWN via Prometheus up metric, (b) Milvus embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) blocking conversation memory writes, and (c) Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig misconfiguration preventing pod-level diagnostics.\nResolution: Diagnostics completed across Prometheus, Loki, and Kubernetes. Three issues identified: (1) PostgreSQL FK constraint violations on user_query_audit table generating 174 errors in 15 minutes — audit INSERT fires before parent message record commits, adding latency to every request. (2) Two OpenAgentic pods DOWN (code-manager and openagentic-synth) with failed health check scrapes. (3) Milvus schema drift — embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) in chat_conversations_v2, varchar overflow in tool_success_tracking, and missing collections. The Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig issue prevented direct pod inspection. Incident classified as automated test validation (VAL-04); findings documented for remediation tracking.\n\nTimeline:\n  [2026-02-21T00:31:34.975388Z] CREATED: Incident created with severity sev2\n  [2026-02-21T00:31:49.041064Z] STATUS_CHANGE: Status changed from open to investigating: Parallel diagnostics initiated: Prometheus up query, Kubernetes pod listing, and Loki error search for agentic-dev namespace.\n  [2026-02-21T00:31:49.456363Z] FINDING: Initial diagnostics complete. Findings: (1) Prometheus: 54 targets scraped, 3 DOWN in agentic-dev (code-manager, openagentic-synth, kubernetes-apiservers). (2) Kubernetes MCP: kubeconfig initialization failed - cannot list pods. (3) Loki: 200 errors in 15min - 174 ERROR-level, dominated by PostgreSQL FK constraint violations on user_query_audit table. Also found Milvus embedding dimension mismatches and varchar overflow errors.\n  [2026-02-21T00:32:46.819421Z] RESOLVED: Resolved: Diagnostics completed across Prometheus, Loki, and Kubernetes. Three issues identified: (1) PostgreSQL FK constraint violations on user_query_audit table generating 174 errors in 15 minutes — audit INSERT fires before parent message record commits, adding latency to every request. (2) Two OpenAgentic pods DOWN (code-manager and openagentic-synth) with failed health check scrapes. (3) Milvus schema drift — embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) in chat_conversations_v2, varchar overflow in tool_success_tracking, and missing collections. The Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig issue prevented direct pod inspection. Incident classified as automated test validation (VAL-04); findings documented for remediation tracking.\n  [2026-02-21T00:32:46.819451Z] ROOT_CAUSE: Root cause: Primary latency contributor: PostgreSQL foreign key race condition in user_query_audit table. The API audit middleware attempts to INSERT audit records referencing message_id before the parent message row is committed, causing FK constraint violations at ~11.6 errors/min. Secondary contributors: (a) code-manager and openagentic-synth pods reporting DOWN via Prometheus up metric, (b) Milvus embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) blocking conversation memory writes, and (c) Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig misconfiguration preventing pod-level diagnostics.\n\nNext steps:\n  - Consider creating a postmortem\n  - Close incident when confirmed stable: incident_close(id)"}],"structuredContent":{"result":"Incident INC-20260221-0001 resolved\n\n🟠 SEV2 | ✅ RESOLVED\nID: INC-20260221-0001\nTitle: VAL-04 Test: API Latency Spike\nService: openagentic-api\nCreated: 2026-02-21T00:31:34.975257Z\n\nDescription: Automated test - elevated p99 latency detected\nRoot Cause: Primary latency contributor: PostgreSQL foreign key race condition in user_query_audit table. The API audit middleware attempts to INSERT audit records referencing message_id before the parent message row is committed, causing FK constraint violations at ~11.6 errors/min. Secondary contributors: (a) code-manager and openagentic-synth pods reporting DOWN via Prometheus up metric, (b) Milvus embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) blocking conversation memory writes, and (c) Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig misconfiguration preventing pod-level diagnostics.\nResolution: Diagnostics completed across Prometheus, Loki, and Kubernetes. Three issues identified: (1) PostgreSQL FK constraint violations on user_query_audit table generating 174 errors in 15 minutes — audit INSERT fires before parent message record commits, adding latency to every request. (2) Two OpenAgentic pods DOWN (code-manager and openagentic-synth) with failed health check scrapes. (3) Milvus schema drift — embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) in chat_conversations_v2, varchar overflow in tool_success_tracking, and missing collections. The Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig issue prevented direct pod inspection. Incident classified as automated test validation (VAL-04); findings documented for remediation tracking.\n\nTimeline:\n  [2026-02-21T00:31:34.975388Z] CREATED: Incident created with severity sev2\n  [2026-02-21T00:31:49.041064Z] STATUS_CHANGE: Status changed from open to investigating: Parallel diagnostics initiated: Prometheus up query, Kubernetes pod listing, and Loki error search for agentic-dev namespace.\n  [2026-02-21T00:31:49.456363Z] FINDING: Initial diagnostics complete. Findings: (1) Prometheus: 54 targets scraped, 3 DOWN in agentic-dev (code-manager, openagentic-synth, kubernetes-apiservers). (2) Kubernetes MCP: kubeconfig initialization failed - cannot list pods. (3) Loki: 200 errors in 15min - 174 ERROR-level, dominated by PostgreSQL FK constraint violations on user_query_audit table. Also found Milvus embedding dimension mismatches and varchar overflow errors.\n  [2026-02-21T00:32:46.819421Z] RESOLVED: Resolved: Diagnostics completed across Prometheus, Loki, and Kubernetes. Three issues identified: (1) PostgreSQL FK constraint violations on user_query_audit table generating 174 errors in 15 minutes — audit INSERT fires before parent message record commits, adding latency to every request. (2) Two OpenAgentic pods DOWN (code-manager and openagentic-synth) with failed health check scrapes. (3) Milvus schema drift — embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) in chat_conversations_v2, varchar overflow in tool_success_tracking, and missing collections. The Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig issue prevented direct pod inspection. Incident classified as automated test validation (VAL-04); findings documented for remediation tracking.\n  [2026-02-21T00:32:46.819451Z] ROOT_CAUSE: Root cause: Primary latency contributor: PostgreSQL foreign key race condition in user_query_audit table. The API audit middleware attempts to INSERT audit records referencing message_id before the parent message row is committed, causing FK constraint violations at ~11.6 errors/min. Secondary contributors: (a) code-manager and openagentic-synth pods reporting DOWN via Prometheus up metric, (b) Milvus embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) blocking conversation memory writes, and (c) Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig misconfiguration preventing pod-level diagnostics.\n\nNext steps:\n  - Consider creating a postmortem\n  - Close incident when confirmed stable: incident_close(id)"},"isError":false},"toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_017bWyJAivjh8phA1Bv4G5Hj","executionTimeMs":28,"targetServer":"openagentic_incident","timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:32:46.854Z"}

