nstraint violations on user_query_audit table generating 174 errors in 15 minutes — audit INSERT fires before parent message record commits, adding latency to every request. (2) Two OpenAgentic pods DOWN (code-manager and openagentic-synth) with failed health check scrapes. (3) Milvus schema drift — embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) in chat_conversations_v2, varchar overflow in tool_success_tracking, and missing collections. The Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig issue prevented direct pod inspection. Incident classified as automated test validation (VAL-04); findings documented for remediation tracking.\n  [2026-02-21T00:32:46.819451Z] ROOT_CAUSE: Root cause: Primary latency contributor: PostgreSQL foreign key race condition in user_query_audit table. The API audit middleware attempts to INSERT audit records referencing message_id before the parent message row is committed, causing FK constraint violations at ~11.6 errors/min. Secondary contributors: (a) code-manager and openagentic-synth pods reporting DOWN via Prometheus up metric, (b) Milvus embedding dimension mismatch (1024 vs 1536) blocking conversation memory writes, and (c) Kubernetes MCP kubeconfig misconfiguration preventing pod-level diagnostics.\n\nNext steps:\n  - Consider creating a postmortem\n  - Close incident when confirmed stable: incident_close(id)"},"isError":false},"status":"completed","startTime":1771633966626,"endTime":1771633967651,"duration":1025,"timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:32:47.651Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01M2pYZiQwovNUTBv2qhrVC2","name":"incident_list","tool":"incident_list","toolName":"incident_list","serverId":"openagentic_incident","serverName":"openagentic_incident","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== Incidents ===\nShowing 1 incident(s)\n============================================================\n\n\nSEV2 (1):\n----------------------------------------\n🟠 SEV2 | ✅ RESOLVED\nID: INC-20260221-0001\nTitle: VAL-04 Test: API Latency Spik